Headed home from Biden event. Making a quick stop to talk about 2016.
77% of Detroit's jobs are 35 mi away from where people live. 49 new buses will help bridge that gap.
In city of autos, 100K Detroiters don't have cars. There's a disconnect between where people live/where jobs are, Biden says.
"It's just that we left Detroit. Detroit didn't leave," Biden says.
Biden is touting all the federal money rolling through Detroit. Dollars for lightweight and heavy metals research, street lights, buses
Biden is rolling up his sleeves: "In America you can challenge orthodoxy unlike any other country in the world."
Biden says city is demolishing thousands of abandoned homes. .@onetoughnerd should get credit for that too, he says.

I remember being with the Dean (@JohnDingell) in this state and seeing factories shuttered. "But that time has past. Detroit is back."
"Detroit is like its people -- resilient," Biden says.
"Detroit isn't just an important city. It's an iconic city." --@VP http://t.co/shQ28b8fgw
